Defendant Raven Presberry in court with attorney Richard A. Sachs.  Molly M Schmidt appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk cmt.
Branch 46 for Branch 23.

Sentencing Proceeded. Statements by parties.

As to Counts 1 and 2:  The court sentenced the defendant to 8 months in the House of Correction on each count, consecutive to each other.  Court STAYED sentence and placed defendant on PROBATION for 18 months.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION
-Serve 45 in the House of Correction as Condition Time, STAYED pending review.
-Parenting classes.
-Mental health evaluation if deemed appropriate.
-AODA assessment, comply with recommended treatment.
-Treatment and/or counseling as determined by agent.
-No unsupervised contact with victims.
-No corporal punishment upon the victims or any child. 
-Pay all MANDATORY court costs, fees, and surcharges including: DNA & DV surcharges during period of probation, failure to pay will result in a civil judgment. 

Filed: Notice of Right to Seek Post-Conviction Relief  Review hearing scheduled for August 7, 2015 at 01:30 pm.
Case spun to Reserve Branch 46.

AS TO COUNTS 1 & 2
Defendant changes plea(s) to GUILTY. Defendant examined as to plea, advised of Constitutional Rights and the maximum penalties. Court found that the defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived rights.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights form, received and filed. Parties stipulate to the Criminal Complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea(s).  Court found defendant GUILTY and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record. Court VACATED Jury Trial date of 5/18/2015. Case adjourned to branch 23 for Sentencing.

Defendant Raven Presberry in court with attorney Richard A. Sachs.  Molly Schmidt appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Case set for Final Pretrial. Parties have reached a resolution in this matter. Received & Filed, Amended Information. Copy provided to defense counsel who waived reading. 
Amended Information Reads:
COUNT 1: Misdemeanor Battery, contrary to Wis. Stat. 940.19(1), a class A misdemeanor.
COUNT 2: Misdemeanor Battery, contrary to Wis. Stat. 940.19(1), a class A misdemeanor.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for May 13, 2015 at 01:30 pm.

Defendant Raven Presberry in court with attorney Richard A. Sachs.  Molly M Schmidt appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Case set for Preliminary Hearing. Defendant waived Preliminary Hearing. Preliminary Hearing Questionnaire and Waiver, received and filed. Court found probable cause and bound defendant over for trial before Judge Grady, Branch 23. Original Information, received and filed. Copy given to defense counsel who waived reading. Defendant plead not guilty. Defense requested case be set for Final Pretrial and Jury Trial. Court ordered case adjourned to Branch 23.  Final pre-trial scheduled for April 22, 2015 at 08:30 am.  Jury trial scheduled for May 18, 2015 at 08:30 am.
